Bayesian A/B Testing Tutorial

Rain Wang

2/13/2021

Bernoulli

Data

  • A is simulated from 250 bernoulli data points with p=0.3.
  • B is simulated from 250 bernoulli data points with p=0.2.
  • p ~ Beta(a, b)
A_binom Freq
0 178
1 72
B_binom Freq
0 189
1 61

Test Result

The probability of P(A > B) by 5% is 0.63.

90% credible interval of (A - B) = (-0.09, 0.3).

Posterior Expected Loss of choosing B over A = 0.01.

Summary

Poisson

Data

  • A is simulated from 250 poisson data points with lambda=6.
  • B is simulated from 250 poisson data points with lambda=6.
  • Lambda ~ Gamma(a, b)

Test Result

The probability of P(A > B) by 1% is 0.18.

90% credible interval of (A - B) = (-0.08, 0.04).

Posterior Expected Loss of choosing B over A = 0.03.

Summary

Combination of Distributions

  • A ~ Benoulli with p=0.3 -> Exponential with Lambda=1/5.1
  • B ~ Benoulli with p=0.2 -> Exponential with Lambda=1/5
  • p ~ Beta(a, b)
  • Lambda ~ Gamma(a, b)

The probability of P(A > B) by 0% is 0.99.

90% credible interval of (A - B) = (0.09, 0.79).

Posterior Expected Loss of choosing B over A = 0.

Summary
